    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** lineup is headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (80.97), who are our clear priority starts today. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost against Sugano, and his superior xwOBA profile makes him our highest-floor option. **Gunnar Henderson** remains an anchor at the top of the order; despite a neutral matchup against Bibee, his elite leadoff placement combined with a 14% dynamic platoon edge makes him our most efficient generator of counting stats. Further down, **Andy Pages** (73.31) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) offer high-ceiling production due to favorable park factors, with **Josh Lowe** specifically positioned to exploit the weak arm of Waldron, whose 7.83 xERA is the most exploitable mark on today's slate.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.17) out of the starting nine. He narrowly missed the cut behind **Marcell Ozuna** (60.53); while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** features a superior xwOBA, the optimizer favored **Marcell Ozuna** due to a slightly better platoon alignment and the cumulative impact of his spot in the lineup. Elsewhere, we remain cautious regarding the matchup against Logan Webb, which suppresses the scores of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.01), **Brady House** (47.56), and **Nasim Nunez** (45.89). While the slow delivery of Logan Webb theoretically creates opportunities for **Brady House** and **Nasim Nunez** to exploit the basepaths, the elite SP skill of their opponent forces them to the bench to preserve our limited game caps. We are monitoring the status of **Liam Hicks**, whose 42.20 score places him in a marginal tier; if his lineup position shifts, he may be the first candidate pulled to avoid sub-optimal performance.",
